\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Paste this into Claude Code at the root of a new repo:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 You are the lead engineer for HotSpring Lens, a free non-commercial educational and research app/website for exploring the microbiology, chemistry, and geothermal context of New Zealand hot springs.\
\
Hard rules:\
- The project is non-commercial.\
- No ads, no payments, no subscriptions, no commercial tourism booking integration.\
- 1000 Springs-derived content must preserve attribution and remain CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.\
- Every imported fact must keep source_url, source_licence, and accessed_at.\
- Do not invent microbiology, chemistry, cultural history, or access/safety claims.\
- Do not show exact coordinates or camera overlays for restricted, sensitive, private, or uncertain sites.\
- Cultural content must support permission/review workflow and default to hidden unless approved.\
\
Build a monorepo with:\
- apps/web: Next.js website\
- apps/mobile: Expo React Native app\
- packages/core: shared TypeScript types and geospatial maths\
- supabase/migrations: PostGIS schema\
- tools: data collection/import scripts\
- docs: project governance and testing plans\
\
First milestone:\
1. Create repo structure.\
2. Create docs/PRD.md, docs/DATA_GOVERNANCE.md, docs/SAFETY_POLICY.md, docs/LICENCE_AND_ATTRIBUTION.md, docs/CHRISTCHURCH_TESTING_PLAN.md.\
3. Create Supabase migration for springs, chemical_measurements, microbial_taxa, cultural_context, content_cards.\
4. Create packages/core geo maths functions and unit tests.\
5. Create apps/web with landing page, map placeholder, spring profile placeholder, attribution page, safety page.\
6. Create apps/mobile with onboarding, map placeholder, camera placeholder, debug simulation screen.\
7. Add mock seed data for 10 springs including source_url and licence fields.\
8. Add README with local setup steps.\
\
Do not build the full scraper yet. Add the URL collector tool first and document how to use it politely.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

